      "@id": "urn:toip:glossary:glossary",
      "name": "glossary",
      "description": "A glossary (from Ancient Greek: \u03b3\u03bb\u1ff6\u03c3\u03c3\u03b1, glossa; language, speech, wording), also known as a _vocabulary_ or _clavis_, is an alphabetical list of terms in a particular domain of knowledge (scope) together with the definitions for those terms. Unlike a dictionary, a glossary has only one definition for each term.",
