      "@id": "urn:toip:glossary:legal-entity-identifier",
      "name": "legal-entity-identifier",
      "description": "The Legal Entity Identifier (LEI) is a unique global identifier for legal entities participating in financial transactions. Also known as an LEI code or LEI number, its purpose is to help identify legal entities on a globally accessible database. Legal entities are organisations such as companies or government entities that participate in financial transactions.",
