      "@id": "urn:toip:glossary:node",
      "name": "node",
      "description": "In telecommunications networks, a node (Latin: nodus, \u2018knot\u2019) is either a redistribution point or a communication endpoint. The definition of a node depends on the network and protocol layer referred to. A physical network node is an electronic device that is attached to a network, and is capable of creating, receiving, or transmitting information over a communication channel.",
