    {
      "@type": "DefinedTerm",
      "@id": "urn:toip:glossary:revocation",
      "name": "revocation",
      "description": "In the context of digital credentials, revocation is an event or status change signifying that the issuer no longer attests to the validity of a credential it has issued. In the context of cryptographic keys, revocation is an event or status change signifying that the controller no longer attests to the validity of a public/private key pair for which the controller is authoritative.",
