    {
      "@type": "DefinedTerm",
      "@id": "urn:toip:glossary:scope",
      "name": "scope",
      "description": "In the context of terminology, scope refers to the set of possible concepts within which: a) a specific term is intended to uniquely identify a concept, or b) a specific glossary is intended to identify a set of concepts. In the context of identification, scope refers to the set of possible entities within which a specific entity must be uniquely identified. In the context of specifications, scope refers to the set of problems (the problem space) within which the specification is intended to specify solutions.",
