      "@type": "DefinedTerm",
      "@id": "urn:toip:glossary:trust-graph",
      "name": "trust-graph",
      "description": "A data structure describing the trust relationship between two or more entities. A simple trust graph may be expressed as a trust list. More complex trust graphs can be recorded or registered in and queried from a trust registry. Trust graphs can also be expressed using trust chains and chained credentials. Trust graphs can enable verifiers and relying parties to make transitive trust decisions.",
